article.headline: Boise St. 85, Colorado St. 76
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- Boise State center Kurt Cunningham scored 18 points and five of his teammates also scored in double figures as the Broncos beat Colorado State 85-76 on Saturday night. Mark Sanchez added 16 points and a team-high 10 rebounds. Paul Noonan had 13 points, Aaron Garner and Ike Okoye 11 apiece and La'Shard Anderson 10 for the Broncos (6-1). Dan Vandervieren paced Colorado State (3-5) with 15 points and 12 rebounds. Marcus Walker scored 13 points and Josh Simmons and Willis Gardner each had 10. Boise State improved to 6-0 at home this season and is off to its best start since the 2003-04 season, when the Broncos won eight of their first nine. The victory was the second straight over an opponent from the Mountain West Conference, while Colorado State dropped its second straight to a team from the Western Athletic Conference. Colorado State lost to Nevada 82-76 on Tuesday, while Boise State defeated Wyoming 86-85 on Wednesday.
